## US-149 — Species Discovery Wired to Open World Exploration

**Files changed:**

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| `config/game/growth.json` | Added `discoveryXpReward: 25` |
| `game/systems/speciesDiscovery.ts` | Added `seenInWild?: boolean` to `SpeciesProgress`; updated `computeDiscoveryTier` (tier 1 fires on `seenInWild` OR planted); added `encounterWildSpecies()` pure function |
| `game/systems/speciesDiscovery.test.ts` | 7 new tests for `seenInWild` tier behavior and `encounterWildSpecies` |
| `game/stores/gameStore.ts` | Added `discoverWildSpecies(speciesId)` action — XP reward, codex unlock queue, toast |
| `game/world/ChunkManager.ts` | Call `discoverWildSpecies` per unique wild species when a visible chunk loads |

**How it flows:** When `ChunkManager.loadChunk` spawns trees in a **visible** chunk, it deduplicates species with a `Set` and calls `store.discoverWildSpecies` for each new one. The store calls `encounterWildSpecies` (pure, idempotent), writes `seenInWild=true` → `tier=1` to `speciesProgress`, grants 25 XP, queues a codex unlock, and shows a toast. The existing `discoveryCount` aggregation in `useGameLoop.ts` (counts `tier >= 1`) automatically feeds the "Keen Eye" and "Codex Scholar" achievement checks — no game loop changes needed.

